column5: about one third of the Barrie Marina is frozen over
alright it looks like virgina beach is ready to go
Is the marina or launches (either tiffen or barrie marina) frozen over.  Wanted to get out on Monday (supposed to be milder) on the wter in a boat.  A normal aluminum 12' boat.
I don't think I'd be going out either in a boat or on the ice at this point.
Good stuff Terry.  I had read that Cooks had frozen over.  Are you looking forward to getting that sled out ??
Sweet!!!  You read to go Carpin again Terry  Joey
YUP I am  all ready to get the new skidoo out for a run to the carp grounds of cooks bay
+8C and Rain for Monday.. ain't gonna help that bit of ice. But is should help knock some snow down or at least hopefully saturate it so it can become slush ice instead of insulation.

-25 here tonight. But then it's supposed to warm up. Highs of -8 to -10 average for the next four days with a 90% chance of snow every day. It's that time of year up here. Mild and snowing, or frigid and clear.
And will help with the walking to the deer hunting grounds.  Terry stop getting everyones hopes up  . We all know, we wont be out there "safely" til mid Jan.
hey I have been on the bay(cooks) most years before Jan  same with virgina beach...so here's hoping
You see,you just cant keep a secret can ya.

I can't think of a year when I wasn't on ice before christmas.......on simcoe!!  It will happen, no worries!! Cooks bay, V beach, Port Bolster....they all get ice long before the main lake does.  Sinker
